als, the previous minister and�we've\nhad approximately 50&nbsp;meetings with a wide variety of stakeholders, including\nthe City of Winnipeg. In fact, the City of Winnipeg has been a part of more\nthan a dozen consultation sessions, including participating in the Bill 37\nstakeholder working group and a full council seminar that my department\nofficials have organized.","index":"00225","speaker":"Derek Johnson"},{"html":"����� And\nthis doesn't include the�<i>[interjection]</i> ","index":"00226","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Order. ","index":"00227","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nJohnson:</b> �regular ongoing discussions between senior officials in my\ndepartment and the senior City officials that touched on this and other issues.","index":"00228","speaker":"Derek Johnson"},{"html":"����� Unlike\nmembers opposite, we are�listening govern��ment and we will toe�take no lessons\nfrom mem��bers opposite.","index":"00229","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> The honourable member for Concordia, on a supplemental\nquestion.","index":"00230","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nWiebe:</b> Despite being given an extra year to go back to the drawing board,\nthis government continues to push through Bill 37. ","index":"00231","speaker":"Matt Wiebe"},{"html":"����� Mayor\nBowman also presented at committee last night, the first time that a sitting\nmayor has done so in nearly 10 years. He called the bill, quote, unaccount�ability\nby design. <i>[interjection]</i> ","index":"00232","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Order. ","index":"00233","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nWiebe:</b> He called it dangerous. He called it reckless. Developers are given\nthe right to appeal projects, but not citizens. ","index":"00234","speaker":"Matt Wiebe"},{"html":"����� As\ncurrently constructed, Mayor Bowman said, Bill 37 represents an attack on local\ndemocracy. He certainly didn't mince words. It shuts citizens out. It overrules\nofficials.","inde